00:36:56,240 --> 00:36:57,958
Regresan high.

505
00:36:59,680 --> 00:37:02,194
You are selling them narcotics.

506
00:37:02,480 --> 00:37:05,074
Methamphetamine.

507
00:37:07,280 --> 00:37:09,191
With all due respect, Don Eladio.

508
00:37:09,400 --> 00:37:10,833
I didn't sell it to them.

509
00:37:11,040 --> 00:37:12,758
I gave them samples.

510
00:37:13,720 --> 00:37:15,073
Samples.

511
00:37:17,000 --> 00:37:19,309
Some businessman.

512
00:37:19,920 --> 00:37:22,912
I gave them samples to give to you.

513
00:37:24,320 --> 00:37:25,992
To introduce you to our product.

514
00:37:26,280 --> 00:37:28,236
Don Eladio, Gustavo meant no offence.

515
00:37:28,720 --> 00:37:31,359
But he... that is to say we...

516
00:37:31,640 --> 00:37:34,473
...could think of no other way to get your attention.

517
00:37:35,640 --> 00:37:37,596
We want to work with you, Don Eladio.

518
00:37:38,880 --> 00:37:42,156
I know all about methamphetamine.

519
00:37:44,640 --> 00:37:47,677
That's poor man's cocaine.

520
00:37:49,200 --> 00:37:54,274
Only bikers and hillbillies use it.

521
00:37:55,480 --> 00:37:58,153
There's no money in it.

522
00:37:58,600 --> 00:37:59,953
May I, Don Eladio...

523
00:38:00,360 --> 00:38:02,271
I am a biochemist by training.

524
00:38:02,520 --> 00:38:04,909
The methamphetamine we make is much superior...

525
00:38:05,200 --> 00:38:08,272
...to the so-called biker crank you know of.

526
00:38:08,640 --> 00:38:10,153
It is crystallised, like glass.

527
00:38:10,720 --> 00:38:11,675
Purer.

528
00:38:11,880 --> 00:38:13,916
And the chirality of the molecule...

529
00:38:14,120 --> 00:38:16,350
...its very structure, is different.

530
00:38:16,560 --> 00:38:18,391
The narcotic effect is far more potent.

531
00:38:18,680 --> 00:38:21,592
This product is the drug of the future.

532
00:38:22,680 --> 00:38:24,432
It'll triple your profits.

533
00:38:25,560 --> 00:38:26,629
Perhaps quadruple.

534
00:38:28,480 --> 00:38:30,357
They're not only good cooks...

535
00:38:30,560 --> 00:38:32,437
...they're great at shovelling manure.

536
00:38:40,000 --> 00:38:43,390
Right now, you deal almost exclusively with cocaine.

537
00:38:43,680 --> 00:38:45,591
But the coca plant can't grow in Mexico.

538
00:38:46,320 --> 00:38:48,709
You are no more than middlemen...

539
00:38:48,920 --> 00:38:50,797
...for the Colombians.

540
00:38:51,280 --> 00:38:55,353
They cut you a percentage for smuggling across the border.

541
00:38:57,760 --> 00:39:01,230
But the lion's share of the profits goes to them...

542
00:39:02,320 --> 00:39:06,029
...despite your assumption of all the risk.

543
00:39:06,800 --> 00:39:08,677
This new crystal methamphetamine...

544
00:39:08,880 --> 00:39:13,556
It's stronger, more addictive than cocaine...

545
00:39:14,120 --> 00:39:16,998
...which means it will move in higher volume.

546
00:39:17,200 --> 00:39:20,033
But most importantly, it's completely artificial.

547
00:39:20,440 --> 00:39:22,431
We can show you how to manufacture it...

548
00:39:22,640 --> 00:39:23,709
...right here in Mexico.

549
00:39:24,440 --> 00:39:27,000
And you keep all the profits.

550
00:39:30,640 --> 00:39:33,518
My men do like your product.

551
00:39:36,800 --> 00:39:39,872
Hector, what is wrong with you?

552
00:39:40,080 --> 00:39:43,356
Why did you not get glasses for our guests?

553
00:39:44,440 --> 00:39:46,317
Go on.

554
00:39:50,360 --> 00:39:53,238
You are quite the talent.

555
00:39:54,080 --> 00:39:58,073
I bet you learned cooking from your mama. Isn't that true?

556
00:39:59,240 --> 00:40:03,836
But... what about the chemistry?

557
00:40:04,560 --> 00:40:06,994
I studied at the University of Santiago.

558
00:40:07,240 --> 00:40:09,310
Gustavo paid for my education.

559
00:40:09,520 --> 00:40:10,509
Oh, really?

560
00:40:11,320 --> 00:40:16,155
I have degrees in both biochemistry and chemical engineering.

561
00:40:16,520 --> 00:40:18,715
With minimal capital investment...

562
00:40:18,960 --> 00:40:21,235
...we can set up a factory-grade laboratory for you.

563
00:40:21,440 --> 00:40:24,512
Train your own people to manufacture large quantities...

564
00:40:24,720 --> 00:40:26,472
...of highly pure methamphetamine.

565
00:40:27,880 --> 00:40:28,835
Fantastic!

566
00:40:32,760 --> 00:40:33,988
Tell me one thing, though.

567
00:40:34,600 --> 00:40:36,556
If you're the cook...

568
00:40:36,760 --> 00:40:38,796
Why do I need him?

569
00:40:41,560 --> 00:40:42,595
Señor?

570
00:40:43,880 --> 00:40:44,949
You.

571
00:40:45,160 --> 00:40:46,639
Businessman.

572
00:40:46,840 --> 00:40:51,516
Why should I negotiate with someone who doesn't respect me?

573
00:40:52,480 --> 00:40:56,871
Who insults me by dealing under my nose without my permission?

574
00:40:57,880 --> 00:41:00,758
Who manipulates me into a meeting...

575
00:41:02,400 --> 00:41:04,197
...in front of my own men?

576
00:41:05,280 --> 00:41:07,475
What do I need you for?

577
00:41:09,400 --> 00:41:11,038
Don Eladio. Please.

578
00:41:11,240 --> 00:41:12,798
I didn't sell anything.

579
00:41:13,080 --> 00:41:15,071
I apologise if you are offended...

580
00:41:15,280 --> 00:41:18,317
...by my method of obtaining this meeting.

581
00:41:18,680 --> 00:41:21,752
I merely took the initiative.

582
00:41:22,760 --> 00:41:26,548
I meant no insult.

583
00:41:27,000 --> 00:41:28,831
Don Eladio, Gustavo didn't mean to offend.

584
00:41:29,160 --> 00:41:30,639
I know Gustavo like a brother.

585
00:41:30,840 --> 00:41:32,068
He's an honourable man.

586
00:41:32,280 --> 00:41:34,874
The most loyal man I have ever known.

587
00:41:35,320 --> 00:41:37,231
He rescued me from the Santiago slums.

588
00:41:37,440 --> 00:41:38,953
He made me the man I am today!

589
00:41:39,560 --> 00:41:41,790
Gustavo is a genius. He will make you millions!

590
00:41:42,240 --> 00:41:45,357
Just find it in your heart to forgive him this one small mistake.

591
00:41:46,200 --> 00:41:47,155
Please...

592
00:41:48,880 --> 00:41:49,835
He's my partner.

593
00:41:50,240 --> 00:41:52,674
I need him! I swear to God!

594
00:42:27,680 --> 00:42:28,635
Look at him.

595
00:42:28,840 --> 00:42:30,273
You did this to him.

596
00:42:31,120 --> 00:42:34,157
Now, look at him.

597
00:42:47,440 --> 00:42:48,839
Listen to me.

598
00:42:49,520 --> 00:42:53,911
The only reason you are alive and he is not...

599
00:42:55,120 --> 00:42:58,237
...is because I know who you are.

600
00:42:59,000 --> 00:43:00,035
But understand...

601
00:43:00,720 --> 00:43:02,597
You are not in Chile anymore.

602
00:43:14,440 --> 00:43:15,634
My advice...

603
00:43:17,000 --> 00:43:18,797
Stick to chicken.

604
00:43:54,520 --> 00:43:56,351
Look at me, Hector.

605
00:44:02,360 --> 00:44:06,717
Look at me.

606
00:44:27,880 --> 00:44:29,791
Maybe next time.
